    System.out.println(vPhoneNumber);
    createCookie(resp, "username", vName, shortExpiry);
    createCookie(resp, "password", vPass, shortExpiry);
    createCookie(resp, "gender", vGender, shortExpiry);
    createCookie(resp, "email", vEmail, shortExpiry);
    createCookie(resp, "phoneNum", vPhoneNumber, shortExpiry);

    // Forward the request to the /Welcome servlet
    RequestDispatcher dispatcher = req.getRequestDispatcher("/Welcome");
    dispatcher.forward(req, resp);
}
```

Now, create a new servlet called `WelcomeServlet` and override its `doPost` method to handle the forwarded request:

```java
import javax.servlet.ServletException;
import javax.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;
import javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet;
import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;
import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;
import java.io.IOException;

@WebServlet(name = "WelcomeServlet", urlPatterns = {"/Welcome"})
public class WelcomeServlet extends HttpServlet {

    @Override
    protected void doPost(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp) throws ServletException, IOException {
        // Handle the request here
        resp.getWriter().write("Welcome, " + req.getParameter("username") + "!");
    }
}
```

With these changes, after submitting the form in your current servlet, the request will be forwarded to the `WelcomeServlet`, and its `doPost` method will be called to handle the forwarded request.

If you want to change the address bar to `/Welcome` and call the `doPost` method of the `WelcomeServlet`, you can use a redirect instead of forwarding the request. A redirect will send a response to the client to make a new request to the specified URL.

To make a redirect, you can use the `resp.sendRedirect()` method. First, you need to store the form data as request attributes before redirecting. Then, in the `WelcomeServlet`, you can retrieve these attributes and process them. Here's how you can change your servlets:

1. Modify the current servlet to send a redirect instead of forwarding the request:

```java
