To display MS SQL Server database table data in DataGridView C#, follow these steps:

1. Create a Windows Forms application in C# or use an existing one.
2. Add a DataGridView control to the form by dragging and dropping it from the Toolbox.
3. Open Server Explorer in Visual Studio and connect to the database that contains the table you want to display.
4. Expand the database and right-click on the table you want to display. Select "Show Table Data" from the context menu.
5. Select all the rows in the table by clicking on the top-left corner of the table and pressing Ctrl+A.
6. Right-click on the table and select "Copy with Headers" from the context menu.
7. Go back to your Windows Forms application and double-click on the form to open the code-behind.
8. In the Form_Load event handler, write the following code:

SqlConnection conn = new SqlConnection("your connection string");
